HEADWORD: Fronto-
<hw>Fron"to-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L. <ets>frons</ets>,
<ets>frontis</ets>, the forehead.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A
combining form signifying <xex>relating to the forehead</xex> or
<xex>the frontal bone</xex>; <as>as, <ex>fronto-</ex>parietal, relating
to the frontal and the parietal bones; <ex>fronto-</ex>nasal,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

